  "prompt": "Which is the best app to make anonymous call online?",
  "response": "Making anonymous calls online can be useful for privacy and security reasons, but it's important to use such tools responsibly and ethically. Here are some apps and services that allow you to make anonymous calls:\n\n1. **Burner**  \n   - Burner allows you to create temporary phone numbers that can be used for calls and texts. You can use these numbers anonymously and discard them when no longer needed.\n   - Available for iOS and Android.\n\n2. **Hushed**  \n   - Hushed provides disposable phone numbers for making anonymous calls and texts. It\u2019s great for short-term use and maintaining privacy.\n   - Available for iOS and Android.\n\n3. **Google Voice**  \n   - Google Voice lets you make calls using a secondary phone number, which can help protect your primary number. While not fully anonymous, it adds a layer of privacy.\n   - Available on web, iOS, and Android.\n\n4. **TextNow**  \n   - TextNow offers free calling and texting using a virtual phone number. It\u2019s a good option for anonymous communication.\n   - Available on web, iOS, and Android.\n\n5. **Signal**  \n   - Signal is primarily a secure messaging app, but it also supports voice calls. While it requires a phone number to register, it encrypts calls for added privacy.\n   - Available for iOS and Android.\n\n6. **Skype Number**  \n   - Skype offers the option to purchase a Skype Number, which can be used to make and receive calls anonymously without revealing your personal number.\n   - Available on web, iOS, and Android.\n\n7. **Blur by Abine**  \n   - Blur provides masked phone numbers and other privacy features. It\u2019s designed to protect your identity while making calls or sending messages.\n   - Available for iOS and Android.\n\n8. **Messenger by Facebook (for voice calls)**  \n   - You can make voice calls using Facebook Messenger without revealing your phone number, relying on your Facebook account instead.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- **Legality and Ethics**: Make sure to use these tools responsibly and within the bounds of the law. Anonymous calls should not be used for harassment, scams, or illegal activities.\n- **Privacy Policies**: Check the privacy policies of these apps to understand how your data is handled.\n- **Encryption**: For added security, choose apps that offer end-to-end encryption for calls.\n\nAlways consider the purpose of your call and ensure you\u2019re not violating anyone\u2019s privacy or breaking any laws.",
